# GitHub Copilot Instructions

## Primary Instructions

Before starting any task, read the main instructions:
- [Project Instructions](instructions.md)
- [Default LLM Instructions](../../docs/llms/default_llms_instructions.md)

## Communication Rules

- Use English for all communication (issues, PRs, commits, comments)
- Never use emojis
- Keep communication professional

## Code Quality

- Follow DRY principles
- Apply SOLID principles
- Maintain framework agnosticism
- Ensure API consistency across languages

## Code Review

When reviewing PRs:
- Check for feature parity across Python, PHP, and JavaScript/TypeScript
- If a feature is added to only one language, create an issue after PR approval
- Use the feature parity issue template

## Architecture

- Drivers: Pure communication, no cache/circuit breaker
- Managers: Orchestrate drivers, lightweight
- SDK: Advanced features (caching, circuit breaker, rate limiter)

